   gradients in a continuous-flow manifold. A programmable,
   computer-controlled pump was used to produce variable, reproducible
   flow-rate patterns that were used to increase gradually the titrant
   concentration-in the flow system. A colorimetric indicator reagent
   allowed the spectrophotmetric detection of the equivalence point. Strong
